ProtoDefines:
. "Let $f$ be defined for $t\ge0$ and let $s$ be a real 
   number. Then the \term{ Laplace transform} of $f$ is the 
   function $F$ defined by \begin{equation} F(s)=\int_0^\infty 
   e^{-st} f(t)\,dt, \end{equation} for those values of $s$ for
   which the improper integral converges."
