ProtoDefines:
. "Suppose $\alpha$ is a nonzero constant and $f$ is piecewise
   continuous on $[0,\infty)$. If $t_0>0$, then the solution of
   the initial value problem $$ 
   ay''+by'+cy=f(t)+\alpha\delta(t-t_0), \quad y(0)=k_0,\quad 
   y'(0)=k_1 $$ is defined to be $$ y(t)=\hat y(t)+\alpha 
   u(t-t_0)w(t-t_0), $$ where $\hat y$ is the solution of $$ 
   ay''+by'+cy=f(t), \quad y(0)=k_0,\quad y'(0)=k_1. $$ This 
   definition also applies if $t_0=0$, provided that the 
   initial condition $y'(0)=k_1$ is replaced by $y_-'(0)=k_1$."
Metadata:
. reference:
