ProtoDefines:
. "\begin{rmlist} \item A function $f$ is said to be \term{ 
   piecewise continuous} on a finite closed interval $[0,T]$ if
   $f(0+)$ and $f(T-)$ are finite and $f$ is continuous on the 
   open interval $(0,T)$ except possibly at finitely many 
   points, where $f$ may have jump discontinuities or removable
   discontinuities. \item A function $f$ is said to be \term{ 
   piecewise continuous} on the infinite interval $[0,\infty)$ 
   if it's piecewise continuous on $[0,T]$ for every $T>0$. 
   \end{rmlist}"
